page.title: 01The East Winch Area
page.content: This block is mainly rural area lying about five miles east of the town of King's Lynn. It contains two centres of population named East Winch, the larger and West Bilney. These villages are inhabited largely by people who work in either King's Lynn or the nearby market town of Swaffham. Both towns are easily accessible on the main road which runs through both villages. This road is named the A47 and carries a great deal of traffic from the Midlands, in the west, to the county city of Norwich and the holiday centre and east coast port of Great Yarmouth. The road divides the East Winch and, after pressure from local people, has recently been limited to 50 mph. The block also contains several farms, two churches, a primary school and a few shops.
